               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440205-name-1132" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1132" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1132" type="surname" value="WATTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1132" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE WATTS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am warehouseman to Henry and John White—I sent a bag out with 14lbs. of tobacco, and these other things, on the 2nd of Feb., by Meadows the carman—this is the bag and the articles—they are my master's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440205-name-1133" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1133" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1133" type="surname" value="MEADOWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1133" type="given" value="ELEAZOR"></interp>ELEAZOR MEADOWS</persName>
                  </hi>. I put this bag into the cart—I was in Whitechapel—a woman ran and told me the bag was gone—I looked at the tail of the cart, and missed it—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> How far had you got from Osborn-street? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Perhaps 200 yards.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440205-name-1134" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1134" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1134" type="surname" value="COCKRAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1134" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS COCKRAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Police-constable H</hi> 143.) I saw the prisoner running with this bag—when he got within ten yards of me he dropped it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did I not fall over the curb-stone? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, you did not.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440205-name-1135" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1135" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1135" type="surname" value="COLMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440205-name-1135" type="given" value="WM"></interp>WM. COLMAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant H</hi> 2.) I was outside the Police-court when the prisoner was brought in—he said in a spontaneous sort of manner, "I am sorry that I have done this act—if I get over it I will take care it shall be the last thing I will ever touch."</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184402050168"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> The words I spoke were, I was very sorry I was in the street, and that I interfered with picking it up, or going near the police-man; I was in Osborne-street; I heard a cry of "Stop thief," and saw some person run from the tail of the cart, and drop a parcel; I took it up, and, seeing the policeman, I was going to give it him, but I tripped against the—curb and dropped it; he cried out "Stop thief;" I got up and ran—two policemen let the other person run up Wentworth—street, and they took me.</p>
